            <section_1687539802
                    jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                    sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                    jcr:title="Examples">
                <text
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                        text="&lt;p>The configuration of the service restrictions is done via matching OSGi configuration files to the implementing service - com.composum.sling.core.service.impl.ServiceRestrictionsImpl - in the respective preferred format. Below are a few examples in JSON format (com.composum.sling.core.service.impl.ServiceRestrictionsImpl.cfg.json):&lt;/p>"/>
                <list
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/composed/list"
                        listType="ol">
                    <section
                            jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                            sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                            jcr:title="Removable Restriction">
                        <codeblock
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/codeblock"
                                code="\{&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;enabled&quot;: true,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;defaultPermission&quot;: &quot;read&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;userOption&quot;: &quot;write&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;restrictions&quot;: [&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;system/service/graph=none&quot;&#xd;&#xa;  ]&#xd;&#xa;}"
                                language="json"/>
                        <text
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                text="&lt;p>Configures 'read' as the default functional constraint for all services and allows the user to temporarily extend it to 'write' if they see fit. However, the service dependency visualization feature is completely disabled.&lt;/p>"/>
                        <text_782664475
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                text="&lt;p>This configuration is a kind of 'self-protection' against accidental changes.&lt;/p>"/>
                        <section_1165668410
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                                icon="info-circle"
                                level="info">
                            <text
                                    jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                    sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>The 'enabled' property allows the service restrictions itself. An 'enabled=false' disables the functional restrictions!&lt;/p>"/>
                        </section_1165668410>
                    </section>
                    <section_435682125
                            jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                            sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                            jcr:title="No Manipulation allowed and File Access Limited to log files">
                        <codeblock
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/codeblock"
                                code="\{&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;enabled&quot;: true,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;defaultPermission&quot;: &quot;read&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;userOption&quot;: &quot;read,write:admin&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;restrictions&quot;: [&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;system/runtime/files=read:^/((sling|launcher)(/logs(/[^.]+\\\\.log(.[0-9-]+)?)?)?)?$&quot;&#xd;&#xa;  ]&#xd;&#xa;}"
                                language="json"/>
                        <text
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                text="&lt;p>The default 'read' restriction can only be temporarily disabled by the 'admin' user. Without the additional rule for the 'admin' user, no user could temporarily disable the 'read' restriction.&lt;/p>"/>
                        <text_415488782
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                text="&lt;p>For the retrieval (display or download) of the files of the working directory, a restriction to log files defined by a corresponding regular expression of the allowed file paths applies.&lt;/p>"/>
                    </section_435682125>
                    <section_1770019131
                            jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                            sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                            jcr:title="Productive Use">
                        <text
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                text="&lt;p>The following example only allows read-only browsing of the repository without ACL access. In addition, all 'system' features are prohibited except for access to the log files. Such a configuration could possibly allow the use of the nodes tools in a production system.&lt;/p>"/>
                        <codeblock
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/codeblock"
                                code="\{&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;enabled&quot;: true,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;defaultPermission&quot;: &quot;read&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;userOption&quot;: &quot;read&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;restrictions&quot;: [&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;core/job=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;core/setup=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;nodes/components=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;nodes/packages=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;nodes/users=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;nodes/repository/permissions=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;system=none&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;system/runtime/files=read:^/((sling|launcher)(/logs(/[^.]+\\\\.log(.[0-9-]+)?)?)?)?$&quot;&#xd;&#xa;  ]&#xd;&#xa;}"
                                language="json"/>
                        <section
                                jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                                sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                                icon="exclamation"
                                level="warning">
                            <text
                                    jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                    sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                                    text="&lt;p>If the installations / updates are done via the package manager, then this feature and the used 'core' features must be explicitly allowed (write), if the default setting is reduced to 'read', otherwise the installation of a package and thus possibly also the change of this configuration is not (anymore) possible:&lt;/p>"/>
                            <codeblock
                                    jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                                    sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/codeblock"
                                    code="\{&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;enabled&quot;: true,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;defaultPermission&quot;: &quot;read&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;  &quot;restrictions&quot;: [&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;core/job=write&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;core/setup=write&quot;,&#xd;&#xa;    &quot;nodes/packages/manager=write&quot;&#xd;&#xa;  ]&#xd;&#xa;}"
                                    language="json"/>
                        </section>
                    </section_1770019131>
                </list>
                <text_487297456
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                        text="&lt;p>The functional service restrictions supplement the restrictions defined via ACLs in the repository. The ACLs continue to apply without restriction and in addition. They are not overridden in any case by any administrative permissions of the nodes tools. The functional restrictions of the Composum Nodes via ACLs on the Nodes components are also still possible.&lt;/p>"/>
            </section_1687539802>
            <section_2061899341
                    jcr:primaryType="cpp:Container"
                    sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/container/section"
                    jcr:title="Status display and status adjustment">
                <text
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                        text="&lt;p>The currently set default restriction is displayed in the Nodes Console in the navigation bar on the right-hand side next to the current user ID, provided that the tool currently used in the Console supports service restrictions.&lt;/p>"/>
                <image
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/image"
                        imageRef="/content/ist/composum/assets/nodes/nodes-service-restrictions-state.png"/>
                <text_16167133
                        jcr:primaryType="cpp:Element"
                        sling:resourceType="composum/pages/components/element/text"
                        text="&lt;p>The 'shield' symbol illustrates the 'read' restriction, a 'wrench' the 'write' status. If a different temporary user option is possible, the default restriction can be switched by clicking on the symbol. A colored background is used if the current status is a temporary user option. It is also possible to temporarily downgrade a configured 'write' restriction (everything allowed) as user to 'read', e.g. to exclude accidental changes.&lt;/p>"/>
            </section_2061899341>
